title: For Sale:  40lb Demolition charge surplus ammo can
postcontent: These are cylinders typically used to store 40lb cratering charges. The top is a screw-type seal that, when turned, will push the cap down on top of the internal cylinder creating an air-tight seal. The screw in the middle can be undone to de-pressurize the container if an altitude change has created a vacuum inside the cylinder. These are made of thick gauge steel and can take one hell of a beating. Internal dimensions are 6.5” in diameter and 23” deep. They weigh about 17lbs with the cap installed. I've got a few of them. They have been used, so there's the occasional small mark or rust spot from being handled. Each is checked to seal tight, be completely rust-free on the inside and have a functioning depressurization screw. ** The included M2A1 can is not included - it is provided purely as a size comparison **
